  "text": "An efficient, channelized drainage system is established fairly early in the season at KS. Little change is evident after approximately day 160, as reflected in KS temporal flux records ( Figure 5 ). Fewer isolated regions of subglacial drainage are likely to exist due to the smaller catchment size, and relatively rapid onset of efficient drainage in the ablation season, as found at Alpine glaciers [CITATION_1] . Supraglacial lake-induced outburst events do not occur at KS.",
